This paper deals with explaining the predictions of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as sentiment analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves evaluating and comparing different methods, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which is a sub-field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves analyzing text data, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
